CatDescriptText: Miss Louise Hicks, 433 Robinson Court, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the District Attorney's office and the courts are exerting all out efforts in prosecuting equal rights cases in which Negroes are the victims?"  Answer reads: "No. And perhaps the reason is because they have been in power so long and just are not interested."
